    "client_msg_id": "62bba35b-67e6-4664-b146-4de2eaa912e1",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Things like handle comments for my blog, or create a feedreader, or an alternative UI for websites I read. All things I tried to do in the past with Ruby or Javascript, but eventually gave up on because of the amount of time they sucked up for ongoing maintenance.\n\nOoh, that reminds me that one idea I've had is a browser for FoC history. I put up a disk image containing all the JSON, and anybody can load it up in Qemu to get a little text-mode UI for browsing history. I think pushing for this one might take care of my angst :slightly_smiling_face:",
