    "client_msg_id": "a0134f71-2474-4cf0-8734-cc55e55a1520",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Thanks for sharing and great to see you here <@U01AD80KMLK>. Just watched the talk, very insightful to see how you take an ambitious project like this and split it up between the two concepts of functions + abstract wikipedia to make it manageable _and_ suitable for a crowd-sourced community to contribute to areas of their interest.\n\nI'm working on a mix of a knowledge graph (roam / notion) and a REPL / notebook, so I'm looking forward to exploring how I can integrate wikidata in the knowledge side and wikifunctions in the REPL-environment.",
    "user": "U01FAFPDFL4",
    "ts": "1616927206.055300",
